contestFinalists.text: "Throw it back—we're fishing for mid-century modern."
"First, I set the mood."
"Looks like the wealth is starting to trickle downstream."
“His words, not mine.”
“We demand time and a half.”
“I’m the new micromanager.”
“He makes us watch this fire-safety video once a year.”
“I understand this is just until the boiler gets fixed.”
“The only other channel is brimstone.”
“I’m still cleaning the glitter out of the truck.”
“Well, of course they don’t exist. Now.”
“I also have a centaur, but it makes people uncomfortable.”
“Arthur, if you can get it out by noon, that'd be great.”
“At least you didn't get the axe.”
“No, not the sword. The test is to pull out the middle drawer.”
“Are you sure the boss is cool with this? It took him six days to make.”
“Most of them have candy. This one's filled with nuts.”
“At this rate, mankind will beat us to it.”
“It’s off the rack. The guy on the rack doesn’t need it anymore.”
“Will you be billing this to the E.P.A. as well, sir?”
“I haven't sold one of these in ages.”
“It sends the other rats a message.”
“It’s New York, buddy. I can make it anywhere.”
“You used to be able to smoke down here.”
“Does he know ‘down’?”
“Can I borrow that? I’ve got to get a cat out of a tree.”
“Sir, I don't make the laws of gravity, I just enforce them.”
“Please, I need time to decompose myself.”
“I’m sorry, but I just got out of a relationship.”
“Well, so much for resting in peace.”
“This explains the art work in the dugout.”
“A lot has happened since your last at-bat.”
“Yeah, I hate the throwback uniforms, too.”
“I’m in the air right now—let me call you back after I land.”
“No, I can’t hold on.”
“Actually, this is my first rodeo.”
“Would you care to hear about our tipping policy?”
“Ignore the screams, sir. I’ll get you a new fork.”
“If you feel a draft, I can close the window.”
“I’ve been told I should go with the white wine.”
“Then one day you wake up and you have ten thousand children and a mortgage that’s underwater.”
“Yeah? Well, I’m also a fish out of Scotch.”
“Sorry I’ve been so hard to get a hold of.”
“Please tell the manager I’ve had an accident on the trapeze in the next room.”
“I wouldn’t. It’s a toupee.”
“Well, at least no one can see your Speedo.”
“Trust me, come low tide everyone will want these seats.”
“On the other hand, we only need half as much sunscreen.”
“You can either complain about airline food or do something about it.”
“Ideally, you want the dough to rise to about thirty-five thousand feet.”
“I call it New York-to-Chicago style.”
“Looks like an inside inside inside inside inside job.”
“What makes you think the Russians were involved?”
“We gotta get the short one to open up.”
“Sorry, kid, but this is the corporate ladder.”
“Stop calling me Dad—you're embarrassing me in front of my friends.”
“Did your taxes pay for this playground?”
“I think it’s safe to assume it contains preservatives.”
“Pretty steep for just a hot dog.”
“No one knows how they’re made.”
“It’s not ye, it’s me.”
“You didn’t mention you wear glasses.”
“Well, I'm sort of between quests at the moment.”
“I hope you’re on a break, too.”
“Honestly, we didn’t think much of it until you showed up.”
“Look down—you just missed him.”
“While it's technically proficient, I find his work predictable and repetitive.”
“When can I let the next batch of leaves in?”
“I'm here to review the fall collection.”
“It’s the convenience of suspenders without the ridiculous look.”
“First time in the Bay Area?”
“You must be the fellow who ordered a friend on Amazon.”
“The real prison is gender roles.”
“No, seriously, let down my hair.”
“It is I, Manbunzel.”
“My other cat is a jaguar.”
“It's easy until someone points a laser at the floor.”
“Listen to this baby purr.”
“I’m more of a sheep hoarder.”
“Could I interest you in three bags full?”
“I don't know how many there are. I'm trying to stay awake.”
“Vinnie would appreciate it if you reconsidered that Yelp rating.”
“Psst . . . two thousand calories . . . no kale.”
“Of course it’s hot. It’s stollen.”
“And now—I've got an old score to settle.”
“My next piece may sound a little bit like the last one.”
“We'll have a brief intermission while I make a pretty big career decision.”
“It's pricier than the clown's mouth, but you save on energy costs.”
“Here we just call it golf.”
“If we time it right, I can get you in this house today.”
“Don’t bring a camera, you said. Just enjoy the experience, you said.”
“He says the real abomination is your cargo pants.”
“I'm sorry, Todd. But he just seems better prepared for what's ahead.”
“My summer body isn’t ready.”
“I still say separate vacations would have been a better idea.”
“I choose to remember Aspen as it was.”
“Now I'll try paper. I apologize about the rabbit.”
“Here's a trick I learned from my lawyer.”
“Watch as I transform this ordinary magician's assistant into an accomplice to a federal crime.”
“It all started when we adopted a highway.”
“It doesn't even stop here.”
“So how did you and Thomas meet?”
“Seems to me that you're the underlying issue.”
“And you say it was a gift from your mother.”
“We'll pick this up next week.”
“Any tightness or difficulty breathing?”
“Yeah, it’s going around.”
“O.K. Now you stick out your tongue.”
“Looking back, we had it pretty good there.”
“I'll bet it's crawling with ants.”
“I wish we’d seen that before we ate Dave.”
“Tell them what happened in the lab, Harry.”
“And she has hundreds of sons about the same age as your daughter.”
“Who are you drinking?”
“Any chance you could turn down the celling fan?”
“You know what? Just bring me back the one with the fly in it.”
“Before you go, describe the iceberg salad.”
“Don't be fooled by her 4.5 billion years of experience.”
“I guarantee in twelve hours we'll see a completely different side of my opponent.”
“And what makes you the expert on global warming?”
“Who is ‘coming around the mountain,’ John? Could it be your mother?”
“We’ll end on that note.”
“There are cheaper ways to find an audience, Jim.”
“Don't let him fool you. He can't read.”
“He gets so dramatic when I lower the thermostat.”
“It was his choice. I wanted cremation.”
“Want to go for a w-a-l-k?”
“All my evaluation said was ‘Good girl.’ ”
“Once you tell them to sit and stay, they actually get a lot of work done.”
“I’ll date anyone with a pulse.”
“We had a good run, Ted, but I simply don’t have the counter space.”
“What turns you off?”
“Are you here about the sublet?”
“If you're going out, we need eggs.”
“Can you believe someone just left it here?”
“Worse than a cold. It's a common cold.”
“The robe is supposed to open in the back.”
“On the bright side, I've got some good news for the Prince.”
“Workplace morale hasn't been this high since we introduced whistling.”
“Let’s keep Clumsy in our prayers.”
“I mean, it's not like mining jobs are ever coming back.”
“It’s about time they settled down and razed a village.”
“Did you see the rock he gave her?”
"I love that no one wears the pants in their relationship."
“Please say you're vegetarian.”
“Remember us from your wedding cake?”
“Well, you're not what we ordered, either.”
"When was the last time you saw either half of her?”
“We know you're guilty. Now we want to know how you did it.”
“And stop referring to the prosecuting attorney as ‘my lovely assistant.’ ”
“Once I gave him a name I didn’t have the heart to eat him.”
“How about some help carrying the groceries?”
“Well, that's embarrassing. How long has it been there?”
“Shouldn’t you be sitting in an ear?”
“Mother wore this color.”
“How do I explain lipstick on my entire suit?”
“Let's just go with the open floor plan.”
“They’re not testing our intelligence. They’re testing our marriage.”
"It's been tested on humans."
“I only like you as a friend, weapon, and means of travel.”
“I’m sorry. I’ve been burned too many times.”
“Look, damsels say all sorts of things in distress.”
“He sounds so much better live than on the baby monitor.”
“I love his bedtime routine.”
“Now we just need to neglect him so he'll have lots of material.”
“It started as a crusade. Now it's just a commute.”
“On thy left, fair maiden.”
“It’s just until I can afford health insurance.”
“It didn’t really bother me until they discovered fire.”
“We never had this problem with the gatherers.”
“The doctor says they’ll be gone in a few million years.”
“I’m a rat. What you need is an ophthalmologist.”
“Trust me, I know the plague when I see it.”
“Don't worry. I wouldn't prescribe anything I haven't tested on myself.”
“For God's sake, Dave, you're thirty-five—just use the stairs.”
“I'd get out of there before the humidity picks up.”
“If you were on time, it wouldn't be this long.”
“Let's let him keep your ball.”
“Kinda puts going to the vet in perspective, doesn't it?”
“You could at least bark.”
“You two seem oddly suited.”
“Yeah, I didn't have time to change clothes after work, either.”
“Didn’t I say you wouldn’t be the only one wearing a suit?”
“You will obey my every whim. Oh, wait—you already do.”
“Look what I dragged in.”
“The ahi. Not the canned.”
“I just invented leftovers.”
“I don't tell you how to gather.”
“Rare? It's nearly extinct.”
“I'm trying to see it from your point of view.”
“If this shows up in National Geographic, we'll never hear the end of it.”
“I always knew we'd wind up together.”
“Yes, Your Highness. The greatest threat is overwatering.”
“My liege, Albuquerque is yours.”
“Well, after you beheaded the groundskeeper, we had to go with something low-maintenance.”
“Well, don't put it on the menu if you can't catch one.”
“Aren't you going to write this down?”
“Is it too late to cancel the salmon?”
“You pinch me one more time and you’re going to find yourself in hot water.”
“I can’t believe you wore shorts. Everyone was staring.”
“Yeah. Like you’re such a great catch.”
“It’s not you. It’s November.”
“I'll wait for you on the car.”
“Seems to me you have problems letting go.”
“Four-story brownstones? They’ll never catch on, not in a million years.”
“It scrape sky.”
“I guarantee he brings up the whole discovering-fire thing within the first five minutes.”
“Publicly, we’re still saying there are no side effects.”
“So the board still has no women?”
“Good, Human Resources is here.”
“Oh, no. I have its little one in my backpack.”
“I think we’re O.K.—honey doesn’t go bad.”
“Stay calm. I think it just wants to be squeezed.”
“He’s brooding again.”
“But will he lift a finger after it hatches?”
“I don’t know how to tell him it’s not his.”
“How much did you spend at Macy’s this year?”
“I’d hate to be on the third floor.”
“It’s a perfect likeness, George. Right down to the hot air.”
“I was stationed at CVS during the war on drugs.”
“It’s the price of freedom.”
“I got tired of explaining each one.”
“Yes, but just a couple of meads, probably more than an hour ago.”
“But, officer, he did not yield!”
“It used to be chivalrous to open doors for people.”
"Please watch your small step."
“I'm sorry, I just assumed you'd want to go up.”
“After the top floor, you're on your own.”
“Well, he did say he’d be back again someday.”
“Great, now they all want a scarf.”
“Invite them in if you want to get rid of them.”
“I'll take this and the granny dress.”
“This is more practical for work, but the zebra is just so fun.”
"Perfect! I'm surprising someone for dinner."
“Yes, that's cool. But it's not statistically significant.”
“Exhibits inability to understand maze exercise.”
“Let’s just give him the damn cheese.”
“It’s like you’re not even trying to shovel on beat.”
“This one’s about a man who wouldn’t buy a snowblower.”
“I didn’t say I would help. I said I’d accompany you.”
“Yes, we seated a potato, but he had a jacket.”
“You’re in luck. A slot for you just opened up in our kitchen.”
“I’m sorry, sir. We no longer serve bread.”
“If there’s a ring in here, Hank, I swear to God . . .”
“Don’t ask for a spoon—he’ll know we’re tourists.”
“I have a feeling I’m not going to like the suggested wine pairing.”
“No one crosses the Pirates of Penn Station.”
“Transfer to the F train and that’ll take you right to the ocean. Then jump in that.”
“Wait till he finds out this isn't his stop.”
“So this is your idea of treating me like a queen?”
“They weren’t usurpers, dear. They just had a reservation.”
“Harry, the whole point of leaving England was to blend in.”
“And how do you feel about how she feels about how he feels?”
“Trust me. You're not alone.”
“Today, we’re going to work on your codependence issues, your separation anxiety, and your fear of heights.”
“They didn’t specify which one, but your insurance will only cover half.”
“Use caution when pulling a wagon, a plow, or other machinery while you’re on this medication.”
“Looks like you’re already familiar with the side effects.”
“I know I don’t look familiar, but, believe me, I eat here all the time.”
“There’ll be several hundred of us.”
“The last time I was here, I swear they tried to poison me.”
“When you wear a baseball cap, everyone knows you’re just covering a bald spot.”
“Just be glad I didn’t come here when I had a ponytail.”
“Could you trim the sides but leave it feathered on top?”
“We’re trying to teach him not to beg at the table.”
“Past the alligator, through the ring of fire, first door on your left.”
“Let’s just say he’ll have what you’re having.”
“We promise there will be no awkward silence.”
“No, you come in on four.”
“Don’t worry. We know how to conduct ourselves.”
“Grounds still warm . . .”
“Americanos.”
“Decaf. They can’t be far away.”
“Of all the things we packed, I didn't think to bring my MetroCard.”
“Of course—we wait forever, then two come at the same time.”
“Apparently, they wouldn't ask for directions, either.”
“Next week, I'll move Heaven for you.”
“It’s mostly water weight.”
“I'm not bringing work home anymore.”
“I heard dinner needed rescuing.”
“The round table is set.”
“Fine—next time you slay the dragon and I'll cook.”
“We’re temps―the eternally damned are back Monday.”
“So now we know what the ‘FIRE’ button does.”
“Try the stairs. This takes an eternity.”
“A group of them is called a band.”
“I can usually identify a bird by the song, but I think he’s doing a cover.”
“Remember when he was just a humming bird?”
“I have to hang up. I’m on deck.”
“All his pitches have been inside.”
“Seriously, you wouldn’t believe my seats.”
“One last thing ...”
“I don’t know about you, but I can’t wait for this day to end.”
“Tell me about a time you identified a problem that others didn’t see coming.”
“Looks like one of them has bad timing.”
“Who’s the clown in the suit?”
“I found something serious under the hood.”
“You’re right. It is easier with the ball.”
“He just loves finding new ways to be indifferent.”
“Remember, whoever drops him gets to dry him off.”
“No, actually I fell off the wagon.”
“And then I find out all the king’s horses and all the king’s men are out-of-network.”
“It’s never over easy.”
“Do you think we should add a password?”
“Damn. Now I’m kinda hungry.”
“He could have just written his name on his yogurt.”
“But they don’t allow dogs?”
“I know it’s not an elephant, but we still need to talk about it.”
“Well, who ever reads the entire lease?”
“I don’t need your approval. I just need you to tie the laces.”
“I don’t think ‘dressage’ means what you think it means.”
“Because they don’t need to be nailed to my feet, that’s why.”
“Between you and me, the owner can’t unload this fast enough.”
“You pay rent quarterly.”
“And, for your convenience, there’s an apartment within walking distance.”
“You think that’s punishment? Try an eternity of listening to pickup lines.”
“Sorry, I said hold the rocks.”
“Do you struggle endlessly through here often?”
“This is why nobody likes to play with you.”
“How’s that door coming along?”
“I’m starting to regret that haircut.”
“The piano's in tune, but the house is a little flat.”
“'Amazon drone delivery,' you said. 'It’s so convenient,' you said.”
“In 2019, I would have been both confused and alarmed by this.”
“Less woofer?”
“That’s perfect. Get out the treats.”
“We should be able to finish the album today, as long as no one rings the doorbell.”
“To Archaeopteryx, spelled just like it sounds.”
“I couldn’t put it down. In fact, I couldn’t pick it up.”
“I’m also a voracious reader.”
“I’m just saying, after this haircut, it’s difficult to trust you.”
“You know, pumpkins are in season, too.”
“I now see why you only get me every other weekend.”
“To be fair, Martha, you did just kill one of their kids.”
“If you ignore them, they go away.”
“It’s odd, you know. They never seem to bother me.”
“And, if you open the window, the view will take your breath away.”
“It’s the closest you’ll get to Manhattan in your price range.”
“Keep in mind the neighborhood is expanding.”
“Relax, take off your shoe.”
“Thank you for agreeing to meet remotely.”
“All my co-workers think this is just a virtual Zoom background.”
“How long can we maintain this balance of power?”
“We’ll show those Ottomans.”
“We can’t be overthrown, but we can be swayed.”
“They tell me your family has been doing lab work for generations.”
“I bet you also had to be twice as smart as the men.”
“And, when you get hungry, the cafeteria is to your right, left, left, right, left, straight, right, straight, left, and then you push on the big lever.”
“During next week’s session, we’ll have you paint yourself into a corner.”
“Welcome to Canada—we’ve been expecting you, have a seat.”
“No, by all means—I want to see where you’re going with this.”
“We demand blanket immunity.”
“Where were you between the hours of beddy-bye and nighty-night?”
“The defense can’t rest without this witness.”
"Every time we attempt a recount, we fall asleep."
"It seems you promised them herd immunity, sir."
"They found out we've been fleecing them."
“I don’t have to. Your neighbor downstairs is going to kill you.”
“Stop fighting it, kid—everyone eventually sings in the shower.”
“Are you gonna talk, or am I gonna have to flush the toilet again?”
“You are a lot bigger in person.”
“I can keep it together during the ceremony. The reception is where I fall to pieces.”
“Great wedding—what’s for dessert?”
“Your meal came with a toy?”
“Evolve already.”
“If that’s a courtship display, I think I know how we go extinct.”
“I thought you said the cloud was secure.”
“Growth has exceeded our projections.”
“Keep climbing—you’ve only reached middle management.”
“A friendly gesture can make first contact go a lot better.”
“As long as we’re up here, we should do the gutters.”
“Can’t wait to see the look on his face when we put these back on the tree.”
“Once tax season is over, you can go back to being the only child.”
“He said you ate his homework.”
“When you’re best in show, you can have nice clothes, too.”
“You were right—putting him on commission changed his attitude.”
“He doesn’t charge as much as he used to.”
“Now he breaks stereotypes instead.”
“I think it’s just a phase.”
“Remind me to close the curtains tonight.”
"Wow, it's a rare full-of-himself moon."
“That’s a rare medium. Well done.”
“Fine, but no flash photography.”
“I could’ve made that!”
“Yes, it does look more realistic that way.”
“Still not level.”
“Maybe it would go better in the den.”
“I could never pull that off.”
"You should see how my owner wears his mask."
"He said I had to wear it. He didn't say how."
“I told you we should have salted the roads.”
“If you turn the binoculars around, the problem pretty much goes away.”
“Quick, stroll for cover.”
“Just as I thought. There’s nothing going on upstairs.”
“Don’t make me come up there.”
“So that’s where all the furniture went.”
“We don’t discuss politics, religion, or gravity.”
“I’m always afraid he will drop in unexpectedly.”
“I just hope they don’t put in a pool.”
“I don’t like to cook in an empty stomach.”
“Not the return to inside dining I was expecting.”
“I guess it’s just us for dinner.”
“Half the flock is still grazing remotely.”
“I think I see the one who’s going to be a problem.”
“Every night, when I try to sleep, I can’t stop thinking about work.”
“Should we get rolling?”
“And to think—a year ago we were all stuck inside.”
“I want one that snows.”
“The classics can be so intimidating.”
“Normally, I like when books come to life.”
“I wish the library would just go back to charging late fees.”
“Oh, hey, I almost didn’t recognize you outside of work.”
“Yeah, well, these are my obsession now.”
“Hit me again with your cart and I’ll hunt you down until the day I die.”
“Apparently, the one you use says a lot about your personality.”
“Is the fire in Times Square or Columbus Circle?”
“Since when did the pizza delivery guy get his own pole?”
“If you’re so civilized, why don’t you use a coaster?”
“I just can’t get past the difference in our ages.”
“I can evolve.”
“So, you’re saying you didn’t miss your last two appointments?”
“Let’s see how you feel on the curtains.”
“Hmm. I’m beginning to see a pattern.”
“Apparently, climate change is getting more serious.”
“I think the weather’s turning on us.”
“Don’t worry, it’s just a front.”
“I’m working my way to a nice corner office.”
“Our company is going public.”
“Honey, can you close the door? I’m in a meeting.”
“They call it kitsch and release.”
“I guess it could be worse. Larry got breaded and fried.”
“I’m a throwback.”
“It’s curb to table.”
“I’m sorry, sir, but we do reserve the right to serve refuse to anyone.”
“Define fresh.”
“He says making lemonade is not an option.”
“They can’t be any worse than the ones life gave us.”
“I do love a good twist.”
“Do you have any experience working in a fast-paced environment?”
“You will still get nowhere—it will just take longer.”
“We’re really looking for someone with more lab experience.”
“So, when did the ‘check mustard’ light come on?”
“Yeah, they’re great cars, but you don’t want to see how they get made.”
“You can use the loaner corn dog while you wait. Can you drive a stick?”
“I hope you’ve come to change the water.”
“The key to happiness? A three-second memory span.”
“If I had the answers, you think I’d be in this bowl?”
“At least you get to travel.”
“I know how you feel. This used to be Florida.”
“Tell me you’ve already eaten.”
“Do you mind? I’m trying to play the drums downstairs.”
“What a coincidence! I couldn’t sleep either!”
“I sent my wife up an hour ago about the noise. Have you seen her?”
“Now, if you'll just yank away the tablecloth.”
“My last boyfriend died in a tragic dining accident.”
“I think I got the waiter's attention.”
"Fine, we can play doubles, but I’m not getting stuck with the horse again!"
"You know that, no matter which one of us wins, this won't be how he tells the story."
"Winner gets the knight."
"His favorite book is 'A Farewell to Arms,' so don't get too close."
"Clyde here handles returns."
"Go ahead, ask him anything. He's a voracious reader."
“I guess I misunderstood when you said your legal problems were behind you.”
“He’s a trail attorney.”
“My husband will never find out about us. He’s on a business trip.”
“Honey, the remote is in your hand.”
“You looked under the cushions, right?”
“Don’t worry about it—I wasn't going to say yes anyway.”
“Oh, go ahead, live a little.”
“Turns out expiration dates do matter.”
“This isn’t what I meant when I said to go toward the light.”
“These drinks go right to my head.”
“We should’ve ordered our drinks straight up.”
“They forgot the little umbrellas.”
“By any chance, are you sitting on a large X?”
“I’d like to report a mutiny.”
“Did you get my bottle?”
“Can’t believe we’re opening for Genesis.”
“Face it. It’ll be millions of years before we’re discovered.”
“They’ll never know what we used our tiny arms for.”
“Most people only have roadside assistance.”
“I said I wanted it out of the yard.”
“He hasn’t proposed yet, but he did give me a written estimate.”
“Yeah, and you never took a pen home from the office?”
“It works fine—we’re just no longer a nuclear family.”
“A minivan just makes more sense for us right now.”
"Don't sell him short. He did solve that crossing-the-road thing."
"We can't seem to establish a timeline of events."
"The cold-case squad says the picture on the left is what our killer might look like today."
“I want to speak with my lawyer.”
“At first, I just wanted a sip of water. Then things got out of hand.”
“Technically, the fish is still in the bowl.”
“Apparently, I was mistaken. He’s not in over his head.”
“He was skating on thin ice for some time.”
“How soon can you start?”
“I so rarely meet a person of your calibre.”
“Will I see you again?”
“Please text me to let me know you got home O.K.”
“Just pretend to give them your wallet.”
“No, it is not better than being broken up with in a text.”
“You had to insist on a quiet neighborhood.”
“So, tell me, do you get steamed easily?”
“Maybe it’s time for you to stop being so good for everyone else and just be good for yourself.”
“And how did being left on the plate make you feel?”
“Mind if I read over your shoulder? I have trouble turning pages.”
“Stuffed? No, actually I’m quite famished.”
“I also love to unwind.”
“Come out with your hands up, wrists straight, fingers gently curved!”
“I thought this was an upright establishment.”
“Looks like somebody needs to be taught a lesson.”
“My client is prepared to walk.”
“He’ll negotiate, but he won’t beg.”
“He may be your best friend, but I am his lawyer.”
“If we forget anything, we can just invent it when we get there.”
“I’ve been packed for ages.”
“These should help me approach your father on his own level.”
"Ideal for parties with no atmosphere."
"You're my fifth middle-school teacher this week."
"I love that people are getting dressed up to fly again."
“You know I can’t stand it when you hover.”
“You’re not the caterpillar I married.”
“Do you have to come in here every time I turn on the light?”
“My other car is a teacup.”
“The dealer said it scored high in crash tests.”
“I wanted a car that would make me feel young again.”
“I'm part Great Dane.”
“It’s got an indoor tree.”
“Don’t you ever feel like they wanted a bigger dog?”
“So far, it looks like no one is coming to the recital.”
“Most fans sympathize with our decision to eat the cellist.”
“O.K., we have a catchy theme song. Now let’s work on food and shelter.”
“No bag. Just toss it in the air.	”
“It’s an appetizer. I’m having people for dinner tonight.”
“I thought you should know, someone left a big mess in the honey aisle.”
“Oh, no! They’re returning him.”
“I was expecting the invasion, but not the audit.”
“I think they want to settle.”
“From the gentleman at the bar.”
“Shall I serve your husband first, madame?”
“I believe you’re familiar with tonight’s entrée.”
“The downstairs neighbors? What is it this time?”
“Or we could get a burglar alarm.”
“Turns out they only check to see if you return the shoes.”
“We can all hear you snoring in there, Steve.”
“You clanked?”
“Your horse is in my parking spot again.”
“That’s gonna cost you an arm and a leg.”
